The paper proposes two modified subband adaptive filter algorithms that are designed to be robust against impulsive interferences. This topic is related to signal processing (SP) and machine learning (LG) as it involves developing algorithms to process and analyze signals. The use of correntropy-based and logarithm-based cost functions suggests that the paper may also fall under the information theory (IT) and statistical inference (SI) categories. Finally, the focus on improving convergence rates and tracking capabilities suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (NE) category.
